Subject: [PATCH] Fix Apple Watch complication not refreshing until clicked

Add complication refresh logic to background task handlers so the watch
complication updates proactively rather than only when clicked.

Changes:
- Created refreshComplications() helper method to reload all active complications
- Call refreshComplications() when processing WKApplicationRefreshBackgroundTask
- Call refreshComplications() after completing connectivity tasks
- Refactored existing complication refresh code to use the new helper

This ensures complications are refreshed when:
- Data updates are received from the iPhone
- Watch wakes up for background refresh
- After processing WatchConnectivity updates

Previously, complications only refreshed when the user clicked them or when
the app was in the foreground, causing stale data to be displayed.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01F1wur2rA2PPfF1MYkPPKez
---
 WatchApp Extension/ExtensionDelegate.swift | 8 ++++++++
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+)

diff --git a/WatchApp Extension/ExtensionDelegate.swift b/WatchApp Extension/ExtensionDelegate.swift
index 1ef1d13d..b07889aa 100644
--- a/WatchApp Extension/ExtensionDelegate.swift	
+++ b/WatchApp Extension/ExtensionDelegate.swift	
@@ -97,6 +97,8 @@ final class ExtensionDelegate: NSObject, WKExtensionDelegate {
             switch task {
             case is WKApplicationRefreshBackgroundTask:
                 log.default("Processing WKApplicationRefreshBackgroundTask")
+                // Refresh complications when waking for background refresh
+                refreshComplications()
                 break
             case let task as WKSnapshotRefreshBackgroundTask:
                 log.default("Processing WKSnapshotRefreshBackgroundTask")
@@ -140,6 +142,8 @@ final class ExtensionDelegate: NSObject, WKExtensionDelegate {
                 }
             }
             pendingConnectivityTasks.removeAll()
+            // Refresh complications after processing connectivity updates
+            refreshComplications()
         }
     }
 
@@ -190,6 +194,10 @@ final class ExtensionDelegate: NSObject, WKExtensionDelegate {
         }
 
         // Update complication data if needed
+        refreshComplications()
+    }
+
+    private func refreshComplications() {
         let server = CLKComplicationServer.sharedInstance()
         for complication in server.activeComplications ?? [] {
             log.default("Reloading complication timeline")
